	(540,'web',14.65,16,4.24,'Cryptonomicon','Neal Stephenson','http://d.gr-assets.com/books/1327931476l/816.jpg','Cryptonomicon zooms all over the world, careening conspiratorially back and forth between two time periods--World War II and the present. Our 1940s heroes are the brilliant mathematician Lawrence Waterhouse, crypt analyst extraordinaire, and gung-ho, morphine-addicted marine Bobby Shaftoe. They\'re part of Detachment 2702, an Allied group trying to break Axis communication'),
	(541,'web',17.76,12,3.96,'The Elements of User Experience: User-Centered Design for the Web','Jesse James Garrett','http://d.gr-assets.com/books/1386924817l/1867.jpg',''),
	(542,'web',11.83,13,3.67,'The Elements of Content Strategy','Erin Kissane','http://d.gr-assets.com/books/1291400563l/9815847.jpg','Content strategy is the web’s hottest new thing. But where did it come from? And why does it matter? And what does the content renaissance mean for you? This brief guide explores content strategy’s roots, and quickly and expertly demonstrates not only how it’s done, but how you can do it well. A compelling read for both experienced content strategists and those making the'),
	(543,'web',17.89,29,4.23,'JavaScript: The Good Parts','Douglas Crockford','http://d.gr-assets.com/books/1328834793l/2998152.jpg','Most programming languages contain good and bad parts, but JavaScript has more than its share of the bad, having been developed and released in a hurry before it could be refined. This authoritative book scrapes away these bad features to reveal a subset of JavaScript that\'s more reliable, readable, and maintainable than the language as a whole-a subset you can use to crea'),
	(544,'web',5.97,16,4.07,'Rocket Surgery Made Easy: The Do-It-Yourself Guide to Finding and Fixing Usability Problems','Steve Krug','http://d.gr-assets.com/books/1348663912l/6658783.jpg','It\'s been known for years that usability testing can dramatically improve products. But with a typical price tag of $5,000 to $10,000 for a usability consultant to conduct each round of tests, it rarely happens. '),
	(545,'web',3.15,23,4.08,'Getting Real: The Smarter, Faster, Easier Way to Build a Web Application','37 Signals','http://d.gr-assets.com/books/1384467434l/447648.jpg','Book report'),
	(546,'web',9.85,4,4.14,'Designing With Web Standards','Jeffrey Zeldman','http://d.gr-assets.com/books/1386923470l/259072.jpg','Jeffrey teaches you to:  Slash design, development, and quality assurance costs (or do great work in spite of constrained budgets) \r\n   Deliver superb design and sophisticated functionality without worrying about browser incompatibilities \r\n   Set up your site to work as well five years from now as it does today \r\n   Redesign in hours instead of days or weeks \r\n   Welcome new visitors and make your content more visible to search engines \r\n   Stay on the right side of accessibility laws and guidelines \r\n   Support wireless and PDA users without the hassle and expense of multiple versions \r\n   Improve user experience with faster load times and fewer compatibility headaches \r\n   Separate presentation from structure and behavior, facilitating advanced publishing workflows \r\n '),
	(547,'web',6.82,14,3.86,'Information Architecture for the World Wide Web: Designing Large-Scale Web Sites','Peter Morville,Louis Rosenfeld','http://d.gr-assets.com/books/1328834902l/70132.jpg','The post-Ajaxian Web 2.0 world of wikis, folksonomies, and mashups makes well-planned information architecture even more essential. How do you present large volumes of information to people who need to find what they\'re looking for quickly? This classic primer shows information architects, designers, and web site developers how to build large-scale and maintainable web sit'),
	(548,'web',16.52,24,4.18,'High Performance Web Sites','Steve Souders','http://d.gr-assets.com/books/1328834938l/1681559.jpg','Want your web site to display more quickly? This book presents 14 specific rules that will cut 25% to 50% off response time when users request a page. Author Steve Souders, in his job as Chief Performance Yahoo!, collected these best practices while optimizing some of the most-visited pages on the Web. Even sites that had already been highly optimized, such as Yahoo! Searc'),
	(549,'web',14.16,18,3.78,'Neuro Web Design: What Makes Them Click?','Susan M. Weinschenk','http://d.gr-assets.com/books/1348027777l/4543746.jpg','\"While you\'re reading Neuro Web Design, you\'ll probably find yourself thinking \'I already knew that...\' a lot. But when you\'re finished, you\'ll discover that your ability to create effective web sites has mysteriously improved. A brilliant idea for a book, and very nicely done.\"'),
	(550,'web',3.23,17,3.95,'Content Strategy for the Web','Kristina Halvorson','http://d.gr-assets.com/books/1347234003l/6355183.jpg','A key guide to delivering useful, usable content to online audiences, when and where they need it most, this handbook delivers the knowledge to plan for and implement a successful online content strategy. It shows designers which tools are available and how to use them to plan for, create, and govern online content.'),
	(551,'web',15.66,1,4.25,'Responsive Web Design','Ethan Marcotte','http://d.gr-assets.com/books/1291401033l/9815906.jpg','From mobile browsers to netbooks and tablets, users are visiting your sites from an increasing array of devices and browsers. Are your designs ready? Learn how to think beyond the desktop and craft beautiful designs that anticipate and respond to your users’ needs. Ethan Marcotte will explore CSS techniques and design principles, including fluid grids, flexible images, and'),
	(552,'web',5.62,15,3.89,'HTML5: Up and Running','Mark Pilgrim','http://d.gr-assets.com/books/1328835014l/6988746.jpg','If you don\'t know about the new features available in HTML5, now\'s the time to find out. This book provides practical information about how and why the latest version of this markup language will significantly change the way you develop for the Web.');
